## 5. Instance-Level DoD Extensions:

The Work Model defines entity-level DoD (applies to all instances of a work entity type). The Operating Model defines instance-level DoD extensions — context-specific criteria that teams add.

    ☐ Define how teams extend entity-level DoD with instance-level criteria
    ☐ Provide templates for instance-level DoD per track
    ☐ Define governance for DoD extensions (who can add, who validates)

---

## 6. Competitive Intelligence Content:

Detailed competitive intelligence (battlecards, positioning guides, win/loss playbooks) is Operating Model / Sales Enablement content. The Definition Model captures structural positioning via Customer Segment's Competitive Context field.

    ☐ Define competitive battlecard template and maintenance cadence
    ☐ Define competitive positioning guide structure per segment
    ☐ Define win/loss analysis methodology and data collection process

---

## 7. Operational Lever Execution:

The Business Model's Lever Portfolio includes an "Operational" lever (internal process, tooling, automation, hiring). This lever maps to the Operating Model, not a specific track. Initiatives with an Operational lever component drive Operating Model changes.

    ☐ Define how Initiatives with Operational lever weight translate to Operating Model work
    ☐ Define the feedback loop between Operational lever outcomes and Initiative target progress
    ☐ Clarify the relationship between Operational lever work and Evolve Track work (process improvement vs. operational improvement)

---

## 8. Track 5 (Evolve) Outputs That Land in Operating Model:    

Track 5 is the structural bridge — it produces outputs that modify both the Work Model and the Operating Model. The Operating Model must be ready to receive:

    ☐ Guidance structure templates produced by Evolve Definition Tasks
    ☐ Ceremony definitions produced by Evolve Definition Tasks
    ☐ Role descriptions produced by Evolve Definition Tasks
    ☐ Define how the Operating Model versions/tracks changes received from Track 5

